0Manuscripts\\\\nfrom Northern Italy ca. 1380-1400: Sources, Patrons, and the Creation of a New\\\\nPictorial Genre\\\\u2019 in <i>Visualizing Medieval Medicine and Natural History,\\\\n1200-1550</i>, eds. Jean Ann Givens, Karen Reeds and Alain Touwaide (Aldershot,\\\\n2006), 51-81.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p></p>\\"}]", "numchild": 0, "content_type": 34, "show_in_menus": false, "path": "00010001000200010004", "url_path": "/home/souvenirs/what-mozart-saw/1770-italy-watermelon/", "expired": false, "slug": "1770-italy-watermelon", "locked": false, "pk": 26, "depth": 5, "first_published_at": "2017-09-23T21:36:24.054Z", "expire_at": null, "live_revision": null}	\N	26	4
