64-1765, Leopold\\\\nproduced both visual and musical objects as souvenirs of Wolfgang Amadeus,\\\\nincluding portraits and printed music, and, in the case of the motet <i>God is our Refuge</i> K20, Mozart\\\\u2019s\\\\nautograph manuscript.</p><p><br/></p><p><embed alt=\\\\\\"God.is.our.refuge : Mozart manuscript\\\\\\" embedtype=\\\\\\"image\\\\\\" format=\\\\\\"fullwidth\\\\\\" id=\\\\\\"5\\\\\\"/>\\\\u00a0</p>\\"}]", "numchild": 1, "content_type": 34, "show_in_menus": false, "path": "0001000100020003", "url_path": "/home/souvenirs/mozarts-producers-souvenirs/", "expired": false, "slug": "mozarts-producers-souvenirs", "locked": false, "pk": 13, "depth": 4, "first_published_at": "2017-09-19T16:04:12.794Z", "expire_at": null, "live_revision": null}	\N	13	2
250	f	2017-10-08 17:48:23.371887+01	{"search_description": "", "owner": 3, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-10-08T16:47:51.559Z", "go_live_at": null, "title": "1763, Mannheim : city planning", "seo_title": "", "draft_title": "1763, Mannheim : city planning", "live": true, "last_published_at": "2017-10-08T16:47:51.582Z", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"id\\": \\"3605a50e-37b7-4c91-bebf-530f938e8ee1\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><embed alt=\\\\\\"Joseph Anton Baertls, Plan de Manheim, engraving 1758\\\\\\" embedtype=\\\\\\"image\\\\\\" format=\\\\\\"fullwidth\\\\\\" id=\\\\\\"23\\\\\\"/><br/></p><p>Leopold Mozart to Johann Lorenz Hagenauer, Mainz, 3\\\\nAugust 1763:</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p><i>Mannheim</i> is uncommonly attractive on\\\\naccount of its regularity; but the houses have only one storey and so it looked\\\\nlike a city in miniature. . . At the end of each street you see 4 main roads\\\\nintersecting, each completely identical to the other. And on both sides of the\\\\nstreets, between the carriageway in the middle and the gutters at the side,\\\\nthere are painted posts on which lanterns stand at dead of night. As you can\\\\nwell imagine, there is no more beautiful sight than a view lit in this way,\\\\nespecially in the 4 main streets, where you can see, for example, from the\\\\ncastle or residence as far as the Neckar Gate etc.\\\\u2019</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"id\\": \\"607b4c84-6a08-40fa-a455-a4567547fed4\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The city of Mannheim owes its modern origin to the construction of the Friedrichsburg fortress by the Elector Palatine Frederick IV in 1606. It is apparently the first modern European city laid out on a grid plan, which the Mozarts are unlikely to have seen elsewhere.</p>\\"}]", "numchild": 0, "content_type": 34, "show_in_menus": false, "path": "00010001000200010001", "url_path": "/home/souvenirs/what-mozart-saw/1763-mannheim-city-planning/", "expired": false, "slug": "1763-mannheim-city-planning", "locked": false, "pk": 23, "depth": 5, "first_published_at": "2017-09-23T21:30:02.684Z", "expire_at": null, "live_revision": 249}	\N	23	3
