b\\", \\"value\\": {\\"quote\\": \\"In London I saw the park and a young elephant, and a donkey that had white and coffee-brown stripes that were so clear that no one could paint them better.\\", \\"style\\": \\"default\\", \\"attribution\\": \\"Nannerl Mozart\\", \\"affiliation\\": \\"\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"id\\": \\"c203dfcd-90de-4040-bceb-acf089be6ea9\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The zebra painted by Stubbs was \\\\u2018the first zebra to be seen in England. It was brought from South Africa in 1762 by Sir Thomas Adams, the commanding officer of H.M.S. Terpsichore, as a gift from the governor for young Queen Charlotte. Two live specimens were dispatched from the Cape of Good Hope . . . but only the female survived the voyage. As soon as she reached London, the zebra was installed in the menagerie\\\\u2019 (<a href=\\\\\\"http://collections.britishart.yale.edu/vufind/Record/1669240\\\\\\">http://collections.britishart.yale.edu/vufind/Record/1669240</a>).\\\\u00a0</p><p>The elephant that the Mozarts saw was presented to George III in 1763. See Hannah Templeton, \\\\u2018The Mozarts in London: Exploring the Family's Professional, Social and Intellectual Networks in 1764-1765\\\\u2019 (PhD thesis, King\\\\u2019s College London, 2016), 145-146.</p>\\"}]", "numchild": 0, "content_type": 34, "show_in_menus": false, "path": "00010001000200010003", "url_path": "/home/souvenirs/what-mozart-saw/1764-or-1765-london-zebra/", "expired": false, "slug": "1764-or-1765-london-zebra", "locked": false, "pk": 25, "depth": 5, "first_published_at": "2017-09-23T21:35:00.172Z", "expire_at": null, "live_revision": 130}	\N	25	3
154	f	2017-10-03 20:55:15.173196+01	{"search_description": "", "owner": 4, "latest_revision_created_at": null, "go_live_at": null, "title": "Engravings of Naples purchased by, or given to, the Mozarts, 1770 (Naples)", "seo_title": "", "draft_title": "Engravings of Naples purchased by, or given to, the Mozarts, 1770 (Naples)", "live": false, "last_published_at": null, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"id\\": \\"6565f8c6-1f19-44cd-a606-b5eafd46dc43\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Just as with the topographical engravings of London, in his letters of\\\\n26 May 1770 (\\\\u2018I hope to\\\\nbring back with me some copper engravings of the sights and curiosities of\\\\nNaples, similar to those I already have of Rome\\\\u2019) and 7 July (\\\\u2018I\\\\u2019ve bought some\\\\nmore engravings for 5 ducats\\\\u2019), Leopold writes of\\\\nengravings of the sights of Naples and Rome that he collected on his first tour\\\\nof Italy with Wolfgang (December 1769-March 1771). The engravings from Rome are\\\\nlost; the engraving from Naples survive (possibly incompletely) in the library\\\\nof the Salzburg Museum. The catalogue card for the Museum Carolino Augusteum,\\\\nwhere the engravings were found prior to their transfer to the Salzburg Museum,\\\\nreads: \\\\u2018Kupferstiche aus Mozartschen Besitz/ Jb. 1850. UB 3227 I / III Seite\\\\n17ff. Pkt 2 a-e \\\\u2018. A further note, in an unidentified hand, reads: \\\\u2018a) Eine\\\\nAnzahl Kupferstiche, welche der Vater Leopold Mozart auf seiner Kunstreise im\\\\nJahre 1763 in London, Br\\\\u00fcssel, Paris und Neapel eingekauft, wobei sich auch\\\\nsein englisches in London gekauftes Gebetb\\\\u00fcchlein befindet.\\\\u2019<a>[1]</a>\\\\nThe Brussels, Paris and Rome engravings do not survive; nor does the small\\\\nprayer book. It is likely that the surviving engravings derive from the estate\\\\nof Mozart\\\\u2019s sister, Nannerl, the inventory of which included:</p><p>\\\\u00a0</p><p>28\\\\