136	f	2017-09-25 20:08:35.516215+01	{"search_description": "", "owner": 3, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-09-25T19:08:18.282Z", "go_live_at": null, "title": "1764 or 1765, London : Zebra", "seo_title": "", "draft_title": "1764 or 1765, London : Zebra", "live": true, "last_published_at": "2017-09-25T11:07:13.361Z", "has_unpublished_changes": true, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"id\\": \\"1ead007e-9517-442c-b5cb-35ff70f3a21f\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><br/></p><embed alt=\\\\\\"George Stubbs (1724-1806), Zebra (1763)\\\\\\" embedtype=\\\\\\"image\\\\\\" format=\\\\\\"fullwidth\\\\\\" id=\\\\\\"25\\\\\\"/><p><br/></p><p>\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n</p><p>Nannerl Mozart\\\\u2019s travel diary, London, 1765:</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>In London I saw the park and a young elephant, and a donkey that had white and coffee-brown stripes that were so clear that no one could paint them better.<br/></p>\\\\n\\\\n<p><br/></p><p><br/></p>\\\\n\\\\n<p></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"pullquote\\", \\"id\\": \\"c95f1882-e3f8-405c-b2b2-a77453098e1b\\", \\"value\\": {\\"quote\\": \\"In London I saw the park and a young elephant, and a donkey that had white and coffee-brown stripes that were so clear that no one could paint them better.\\", \\"style\\": \\"default\\", \\"attribution\\": \\"Nannerl Mozart\\", \\"affiliation\\": \\"\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"id\\": \\"c203dfcd-90de-4040-bceb-acf089be6ea9\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The zebra painted by Stubbs was \\\\u2018the first zebra to be seen in England. It was brought from South Africa in 1762 by Sir Thomas Adams, the commanding officer of H.M.S. Terpsichore, as a gift from the governor for young Queen Charlotte. Two live specimens were dispatched from the Cape of Good Hope . . . but only the female survived the voyage. As soon as she reached London, the zebra was installed in the menagerie\\\\u2019 (<a href=\\\\\\"http://collections.britishart.yale.edu/vufind/Record/1669240\\\\\\">http://collections.britishart.yale.edu/vufind/Record/1669240</a>).\\\\u00a0</p><p>The elephant that the Mozarts saw was presented to George III in 1763. See Hannah Templeton, \\\\u2018The Mozarts in London: Exploring the Family's Professional, Social and Intellectual Networks in 1764-1765\\\\u2019 (PhD thesis, King\\\\u2019s College London, 2016), 145-146.</p>\\"}]", "numchild": 0, "content_type": 34, "show_in_menus": false, "path": "00010001000200010003", "url_path": "/home/souvenirs/what-mozart-saw/1764-or-1765-london-zebra/", "expired": false, "slug": "1764-or-1765-london-zebra", "locked": false, "pk": 25, "depth": 5, "first_published_at": "2017-09-23T21:35:00.172Z", "expire_at": null, "live_revision": 130}	\N	25	3
